 Clergy credit

 Seoul, July 1: (Reuters): One of South Koreas top banks has rolled out a new credit card for Protestant clergy that will give them breaks on Bible purchases and allow them to gather bonus points they can turn into donations for their churches.

 The state-run Industrial Bank of Korea has introduced its I am Pastor card that will give clergy a few dollars off when they purchase religious books at certain websites.

 China rap

 Beijing (Reuters): China plans to sack all officials found to have secretly kept and supported mistresses, the state media has said. It is a misunderstanding that officials who have mistresses would only be sacked when the situation is serious, Beijing News quoted a personnel ministry official as saying. 




